<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>赛琪 |关于人类状况</title><link>https://psyche.co</link><description>Psyche 是 Aeon 的一本数字杂志，通过心理学、哲学和艺术阐明人类状况。</description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 18:12:53 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>心依然嗡嗡作响</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/706a0e80-e38b-43ab-ad6e-8c9edf1db1a4/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;温柔地审视五位面临巨大困难的母亲，她们开始打破毒瘾、贫困和忽视的循环&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>在充满尼安德特人骨骼的洞穴中挖掘答案</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="在洞穴地面上挖掘的浮雕中可以看到头骨的骨骼轮廓" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/9ed85d80-8a3d-44e1-a3db-128c02bb1398/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;当一组研究人员返回一个被认为是尼安德特人埋葬地的伊拉克洞穴时，他们发现了以下内容&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何克服数学焦虑</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/9cd1d819-0617-4a24-9d7d-ce3e678bca7b/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;对数学感到压力是很常见的，但没有必要。只要采取正确的方法，您甚至可以开始享受它&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如果思考是理性的，那么是什么让过度思考变得非理性呢？</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="从后面看到一位女士一边打电话一边心不在焉地用手梳理着头发" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/e9977038-e9aa-4b85-bdf4-6c3e63b6c448/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;关于过度思考的哲学视角为焦虑和强迫症所涉及的心理过程提供了新的见解&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——巴勃罗·胡巴赫·哈尔勒&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么当你能在艺术中看到自己时，艺术看起来更美丽</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/5611e3e8-feae-429e-b262-4f0d569b64cb/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;研究表明，当艺术品在某种程度上与个人相关时，人们会觉得艺术品更美观&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——马特·休斯顿&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>一个迷失男孩的歌</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/0c1dc5e0-4d2b-479e-80c3-acdb164e64b3/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;一场令人愉快、古怪的蜡铸成长冒险，唱诗班男孩失去了声音，但却找到了一个新的社区&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Oct 2023 05:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>敬畏是美德，比勇敢更重要</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="俯视一个人在水面上的码头边缘保持平衡的脚趾和脚的特写镜头" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/1c8697cc-38fe-447b-8b9c-c83f2e4a7c75/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;恐惧不是敌人，而是一种真实而合理的情绪。为了真正支持另一个人的恐惧，让他们发出自己的声音&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——阿米·哈尔滨&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何摆脱气候冷漠</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="一对夫妇坐在遮阳伞下的躺椅上，凝视着大海" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/6f7ba40a-0a09-4e83-a7c1-26fb054ed4d5/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;您是否意识到气候紧急情况，但却发现自己把目光移开？以下是如何激发动力并立即采取行动&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——伊丽莎白·克里普斯&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>当正念遇到资本主义时，它就会迷失方向</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/907d447f-0d1f-4722-94e3-345c3d88c094/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;现代正念商业剥夺了实践的精神意义和实用价值&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——克里斯·惠特利&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 17 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为了改善你的生活，请考虑改变你的性格</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="两名身穿粉色和白色兔子服装的妇女在地铁站入口外喝啤酒。其中一个看起来闷闷不乐" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/fa0c2e25-daf3-41bb-9ee1-c0590de812a8/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;新的研究支持这样的观点：有意识地发展某些特征不仅是可能的，而且会带来好处&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——克里斯蒂安·贾勒特&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item></channel></rss>